Package io.github.eutro.wasm2j.core.conf.itf

Interface CallingConvention

All Known Implementing Classes:
BasicCallingConvention
public interface CallingConvention
A convention that defines how parameters are passed to, and arguments received from, a function, and how values (possibly many) should be returned.

A calling convention converts from (resp. to) a WebAssembly function type to (resp. from) a Java method type, handling passing of parameters and the packing/unpacking of multiple returns.

There is therefore the distinction between the WebAssembly function, its type, arguments and return values, and the actual "raw" Java method, its arguments, its return value, and its type.

Currently, the only usable calling convention is BasicCallingConvention.

See Also:
  • WirJavaConventionFactory.Builder.setCallingConvention(CallingConvention)

    • passArguments

      List<Var> passArguments(IRBuilder ib, List<Var> args, TypeNode funcType)
      For a given function type, emit code to convert the given WebAssembly args (as given to a WasmOps.CALL_INDIRECT instruction) to how they should be passed to the method handle implementing the raw Java function.

      This will be in the caller of the function.

      Parameters:

      args - The argument list.
      funcType - The type of the function.
      Returns:
      The list of raw Java arguments.

    • emitCallIndirect

      default void emitCallIndirect(IRBuilder ib, Effect effect)
      Emit code to call a function reference.

      The effect will have an instruction of type WasmOps.CALL_INDIRECT,
      with as many arguments as the function has parameter types, prefixed by the function reference already retrieved from the table;
      it will assign to as many variables as the function has return types.

      Parameters:
      ib - The instruction builder.
      effect - The effect.
